data.title: good bbq
data.text: Willie B's has been an Edinburg BBQ place to eat for a long long time.  It is good bbq.  The plates are huge and the price is ok.

data.title: Nice place, not the best BBQ but its good beef.
data.text: The beef is really good, but the price is much higher than it should be. The sweet tea is good and so are the sides.

data.title: Was given a gift certificate, would return and pay.
data.text: There are many Barbeque places to choose from in the Mcallen, Pharr, and Edinburg area.  This one is a favorite of many people and having visited I can see why.  The food was very good and the prices also.

data.title: Great BBQ
data.text: My wife and I wnet her just after we had our second son. We went during lunch just to eat and go. We love to find a family run place that has great food. The staff was very friendly and the place has that messy bbq look. it's a relaxed place and the food was very good. I enjoyed a brisket sandwich and My wife had the brisket potato. it was a little too greasy but overall we really enjoyed it.

data.title: Great Texas BBQ
data.text: Family-run smokehouse with excellent brisket, turkey, and sausage. Their BBQ baked potatoes are fantastic with chopped brisket piled high.

data.title: Barbeque and Catfish?
data.text: OK, it is obvious from the name that this is a barbecue place but most people do not realize that on Fridays they serve some delirious cat fish. I have eaten barbecue all over Texas and this is some of the best brisket and sausage in Texas and certainly in the RGV. But what blew me away and keeps me going back is the catfish. I grew up in East Texas and lived in Lufkin (hush-puppy capital of the world) and I know good catfish. My first plate I expected to be "fatty" like so many non-catfish places are but this was excellent. If you like catfish or just want to try something different, try thr Friday catfish platter. You'll be glad you did. I have to warn you though, some people do not appreciate good catfish. My wife is one of those people but she does love barbecue. So Willie B's has us covered.

data.title: Great smoke house
data.text: The food was really good and had a great smoky taste!! The decor is a little on the old side but I think that's the look they are going for with the tagged walls and cafeteria style tables ... We were in and out within 30 min with full bellys and happy taste buds for 25 bucks including drinks for 2 people :) were happy with our new find :)

data.title: Dining at Willie's BBQ
data.text: We seldom go back to this place and no longer recommend it. After reading the ratings, the comments, I have to agree. This restaurant is on the decline. In its hay day is was fantastic, but no more. The food portions got smaller and smaller, the prices got higher and higher. They are pricing themselves out of business. The staff is friendly, depending on who you get. There is one guy there that is a real grouch. Prices are not mid range, and definitely not worthy of a fine dining classification. But yes, very pricey.

data.title: You cannot get better barbeque anywhere
data.text: this place looks a bit rough on the outside, but if barbeque is what you want, and you're lucky enough to be in south Texas, you need to take the time to go to Willie B's for lunch or dinner.  First, all his recipes are from his family, and don't attempt to change them if you happen to work there, because you'll be shown the door. In other words, Willie knows how to make BBQ, and don't try and tweak it.  He smokes all his meat in pecan; OH MY God, that was good.  The sides are pretty creative also.  I never had cram corn with jalapenos, and I'm not a jalapeno fan, but this was good.  I had the brisket and it was tender, and flavorful.  When I die, I hope heaven is Willie B's. I also got to try his ribs and they were also great.  Enjoy.  I did.

data.title: Food is not fresh
data.text: This was once a good place to eat. Now that business has slowed, the food is not as fresh as it should be. I would rather drive 30min to Willie B's in Alamo (the original restaurant) to eat some fresh and tasty BBQ.

data.title: Food Good, Ambiance Not so Good
data.text: BBQ and side dishes are very tasty.  Environment is a little too funky and doesn't feel safe. I stopped going for this reason, and there are other options available. We are in Texas after all! However, lots of professional looking people eat here during the day, probably lawyers since the place is near the County Courthouse.

data.title: Heavenly Pecan Smoked chopped beef
data.text: A RARITY for the Rio Grande Valley bar b que lovers the real actual  PECAN smoked wood shipped in from east Texas by Willie himself fantastic Chopped beef SANDWICHES. Don't listen to any bad reviews this place is kick butt delicious authentic East Texas  inspired down home cooking. If your hungry for a fajita taco try his black angus pecan smoked taco. You'll be hooked. Tell them CAPTAIN Cliff Fleming sent you.  I

data.title: Where's the meat???
data.text: Over-priced and not worth the money, service is not a word this establishment is aware of.  Stand in line to place your order, grab your own bottle of whatever you are drinking.  AND, they have a tip jar...for who?

data.title: on the decline
data.text: I've been coming here for years. There is a history to this place. There is a second Willie B's in Alamo or Pharr which is sub par compared to this one. However, over the years it use to be a hotspot to go for your bbq. Prices were great and the portions were good. Over time though the prices i think dont' justify what they give you now. Popular items are Brisket burgers and loaded JUMBO potatoe's. which your choice of meat on it. My fav was the brisket burgers which use to be $3.50, and of course over times inflation change costs and what not but now its over $6bucks for the burger alone and the chopped are scant. Also it heavily depends who cuts and chops your portions. They use to be good about chopping off the fat off the brisket all the time. But now a days, they leave in the fat and weigh the portion before they put it in the burger buns. I also use to love dinning in cause it has a rustic theme to it but it really shows its age when you see roaches scaling the walls. Its an older building so it was bound to happen. I use to visit this place in the 90s but now not so much.

data.title: Great place to eat for lunch
data.text: Great food @ lunch time, but dinner hours are questionable. I love the food and the customer service during my lunch break, but I have gone at dinnertime several times and left disappointed because they weren't open like the were scheduled on the door.

data.title: Has gone downhill
data.text: The reviews looked great, but we were rather disappointed with this place.  The pork was dry and not very smokey, and the sauce was nothing special.  The prices are quite high for this sort of place, $15 for a lunch-sized BBQ in a low rent part of town seems high to me.

data.title: BEST BBQ IN THE RGV
data.text: As I drove by I could smell the pit cooking so I just had to turn around. Luckily I did, I got to try the famous loaded baked potatoes with brisket on top! MMMM..delicious!! I will be back again.
